{
  "texts": [
    "The base encoder network e(.)",
    "is an embedding layer followed by a series of conv1D layers and is responsible for extracting a representation vector h from the augmented SMILES.",
    "The embedding layer maps each atom in the SMILES to a continuous vector of size 116, using a vocabulary of 148 elements that includes all atoms of the periodic table and some special characters, such as @ and \\, which are used to construct the SMILES.",
    "We use the Rectified linear unit activation function (ReLU), and dropout and batch normalization layers are placed between the convolutional layers of the neural network layers.",
    "The projection head g(.)"
  ]
}